Post-Doctoral Researcher in:
Homotopy Type Theory / Category Theory / Type Theory / Homotopy Theory
Carnegie Mellon University / Philosophy Department=20

The research group in Homotopy Type Theory at Carnegie Mellon University =
seeks a=20
Post-Doctoral Researcher for one academic year, with a possibility of =
renewal. =20
Position to begin September 2019, or possibly later, and continue for 9 =
months. =20
Candidates should have a PhD and research experience in a relevant area=20=

and a desire to collaborate with the existing research group,=20
which consists of several faculty members, postdocs, and graduate =
students.=20
The position is contingent on the expected approval of funding.

Questions about the position may be directed to Steve Awodey, =
awodey@cmu.edu.
Candidates should submit a CV and a brief research statement to =
CMUPhilosophy@andrew.cmu.edu.

